&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mental Health Band 3 Ward Administrator&lt;/strong&gt; – Rose Ward, Prospect Park Hospital, Reading&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;An exciting 12 month secondment/fixed term contract Ward Administrator opportunity has arisen on Rose Ward at Prospect Park Hospital. If you are looking to progress your mental health career pathway, our acute wards can offer you a great environment that will enable you to develop your skills &amp; confidence as a Ward Administrator. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Rose is a mixed 22 bed Acute Ward that &lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;provides care for vulnerable adults. Based in Reading, located close to the amenities of the town centre and a leafy park, the ward works closely with patients and families to help them to identify their needs and participate actively in their care, providing a place of empathy, kindness and compassion. We have created a culture where everyone has a voice and where service users and staff collaborate to make positive change.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Highly organised, you will enjoy working in a busy environment and will have demonstrable office work experience. You’re able to adapt at problem-solving and have excellent oral and written communication and people skills. Willing to learn, you will show initiative and be highly motivated, and feel confident in handling confidential and sensitive information with care and respect. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;We’d love to welcome you into our friendly and enthusiastic team, where you will play a vital role in helping us achieve our ambitions to become a ‘Centre of Excellence’.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Job&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The post holder is required to provide administrative and clerical support to an adult acute ward. The post holder will work as a key member of the multi-disciplinary team and assist in the promotion of high-quality service.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To have effective communication with all disciplines, patients and relatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To accept tasks under the direct supervision of the professional nursing staff, maintaining close liaison with those concerned and reporting back.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To monitor stationary, stock food stores, non-clinical stores and re-order as necessary, to liaise with ISS regarding work repairs/faults&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To organise, collate and maintain nursing and medical files for in-patients.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Some of the benefits of joining our team:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Agenda for Change Salary ranging from &lt;strong&gt;£19,737 to £21,142&lt;/strong&gt; per annum&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible working opportunities and a strong emphasis on your work, life balance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Annual leave – 27 days for new starters, plus bank holidays. Increasing to 29 days after 5 years and 33 days after 10 years NHS service. Pro rata for part time staff&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent learning and development opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Salary sacrifice scheme for a new car&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generous maternity, paternity and adoption leave for eligible staff&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced IT enablement and support&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Confidential telephone care service providing independent support and advice for staff.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;And so much more&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The “must haves” for you to be considered for this role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good general qualifications, including English and Maths at GCSE Grade C or above&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;It literate&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good oral and written communication&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Previous experience of office work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrable understanding of an acute mental health environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you recognise yourself in these requirements, we would recommend you apply today!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are happy to answer any questions that you may have. Please don’t hesitate to call: Mark Wiltshire on 0118 960 5391 or email: Mark.Wiltshire@berkshire.nhs.uk who’ll be delighted to help.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
